Dialogue: 0,0:00:00.00,0:00:05.46,Title,,0000,0000,0000,,FAMOUS DETECTIVE HOLMES
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.08,0:01:40.98,Ep Title,,0000,0000,0000,,The Monster of the Thames River
Dialogue: 0,0:01:51.41,0:01:53.85,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, the fog is getting very thick!\NKeep a sharp eye out!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.08,0:01:55.38,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes Sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.03,0:02:08.43,Behind the Scenes,,0000,0000,0000,,What?! What's wrong?!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.20,0:02:12.63,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Something bumped against\Nthe bottom of the ship!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.10,0:02:18.87,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Stop!\NNo! Go forward!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.14,0:02:20.04,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.35,0:02:33.98,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Everybody!\NAbandon ship right now!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.09,0:02:35.38,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Abandon ship!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.35,0:03:01.75,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,The Monster of the Thames River\Nattacked a cargo ship.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.85,0:03:03.94,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,What do you think of that, Mr. Holmes?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.45,0:03:05.78,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,What do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.89,0:03:10.69,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,The monster made thunderous sounds\Nand swallowed the ship with one gulp.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.96,0:03:15.49,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Dinosaurs are supposed to have been\Nextinct for 70 million years.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.83,0:03:19.70,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,However, I wouldn't doubt it if\Nsome had miraculously survived.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:20.20,0:03:22.03,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,I think it could be possible.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.84,0:03:26.27,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Watson, as a scientist,\Nyou are a surprising romantic.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.41,0:03:27.43,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,How amusing.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.54,0:03:29.57,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, it's just kind of a dream.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.14,0:03:33.74,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,I think it's not so strange to believe\Nthat dinosaurs have survived.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.15,0:03:39.61,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,But, I doubt they want\Nto eat cargo ships.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.19,0:04:15.85,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,That was wonderful, David!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.96,0:04:17.79,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Bravo! Bravo!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.99,0:04:19.96,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Encore! Encore!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.80,0:04:23.63,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,David, encore!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:23.80,0:04:24.99,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,You're embarrassing me.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.10,0:04:26.07,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't be shy.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.37,0:04:28.93,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,You won a gold medal\Nat the last competition.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.00,0:04:30.47,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,You have great skill.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:30.64,0:04:32.26,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Please play for everybody\None more time.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.04,0:04:36.10,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,I understand, Mary.\NThen, I'll play for you with love.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.14,0:05:08.40,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Operation! Stand by!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.11,0:05:15.17,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Professor, we're ready!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.58,0:05:17.02,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, let's begin!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.22,0:05:18.21,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,- Yes, sir!\N- Yes, sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.65,0:05:20.88,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,The Loch Ness Monster\Ncomes out now!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.46,0:05:24.55,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Bravo!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.76,0:05:28.99,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you very much.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.13,0:05:29.75,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.10,0:05:31.09,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.70,0:05:37.47,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Cheers to that beautiful\Nsong and your love!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.94,0:05:38.77,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Here!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.34,0:05:41.33,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, thank you!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:41.48,0:05:42.57,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.11,0:05:45.51,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, it's already late.\NWe have to go home now.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:45.85,0:05:47.58,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Have a safe trip!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.78,0:05:49.25,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,- Good luck!\N- Good luck!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:03.30,0:06:04.29,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,What is that?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.44,0:06:09.63,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,A monster!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.99,0:06:28.85,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,The oar!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.09,0:06:30.15,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,David!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.20,0:06:36.42,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Swim to the shore!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.80,0:06:38.96,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,David!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.27,0:06:42.53,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Mary!!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.84,0:06:45.07,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,David!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.94,0:06:48.34,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,It's dangerous, Miss!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.61,0:06:49.77,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,David! David!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.94,0:06:51.31,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Where are you, David?!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.58,0:06:53.74,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,David!!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.60,0:07:16.43,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Haven't you found anything yet?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.54,0:07:18.27,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, it's too dark here.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.64,0:07:19.76,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, I felt something!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.87,0:07:20.64,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.22,0:07:33.78,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Search more thoroughly!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.79,0:07:37.65,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,David...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.70,0:07:44.53,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:45.10,0:07:47.07,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry to bother you\Nso early in the morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.33,0:07:49.60,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,I really wanted to see Mr. Holmes.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.80,0:07:51.93,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Here, come inside please.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.37,0:07:53.70,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.21,0:07:57.18,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,May I see him right now?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.78,0:08:00.27,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, he's waking up about now.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:09.79,0:08:13.38,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Inspector Lestrade searched\Nfor him down river.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.63,0:08:16.62,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,However, they couldn't\Nfind the slightest trace.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.16,0:08:20.33,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,But David did not sink to\Nthe bottom of the river.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.37,0:08:25.43,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,I know David is still alive.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.77,0:08:26.74,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Miss Mary.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.21,0:08:31.23,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,We made a promise to be\Nmarried in the future.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.08,0:08:35.48,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,David will keep that promise,\Nno matter what happens.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.35,0:08:40.68,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Mr. Holmes, I also believe...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.82,0:08:42.52,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,in their bonds of love.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.62,0:08:44.95,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Excuse me.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.76,0:08:46.89,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Mr. Holmes!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.20,0:08:50.39,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Can you give me 10 minutes\Nto prepare to leave?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.30,0:08:53.10,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,No make that 5 minutes.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.97,0:08:56.70,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you Mr. Holmes.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.18,0:09:12.62,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't see anything strange.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.93,0:09:28.33,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,We did it!\NWe did it!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.57,0:09:31.73,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,This time, not even Detective\NHolmes will figure out this mystery!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.61,0:09:34.37,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Ouch!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.61,0:09:37.37,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Who put a table here?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:37.94,0:09:39.47,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,You did.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.91,0:09:41.97,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,What? Did I? That can't be!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.02,0:09:50.22,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,You said we have to prepare\Nthe party to celebrate.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.42,0:09:52.45,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, yeah, I remember that.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.73,0:09:54.75,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Then, let's make a toast.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.06,0:09:56.82,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Open the champagne.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.10,0:10:00.50,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,This is tight.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.87,0:10:02.30,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Hurry it up!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.91,0:10:07.50,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,What the?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:11.95,0:10:13.50,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Smiley, what's wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.28,0:10:18.68,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,This is like a dream,\Nall this gourmet food.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:22.26,0:10:23.75,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,I understand Smiley.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:24.62,0:10:28.53,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,All we've been eating is the hard\Ncrusts of bread with water.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.73,0:10:30.70,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,But!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.57,0:10:35.69,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you for being patient\Nand working for me to this day.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.97,0:10:36.99,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,I appreciate it.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.10,0:10:38.07,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Professor!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.41,0:10:40.31,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,I won't let you suffer any more.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.07,0:10:44.34,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Goodbye to sorrow,\Nhello to happiness.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.51,0:10:46.88,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,We'll have wonderful days\Ncontinuously from now on!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.28,0:10:49.31,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,As long as the Thames River exists!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:51.75,0:10:53.55,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Our victory is...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:55.82,0:10:57.31,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,That's really noisy!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.09,0:10:59.52,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,It's the brat!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.69,0:11:01.22,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you want me to shut him up?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.36,0:11:02.23,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, wait...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.36,0:11:05.23,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,he's a rare guest.\NLet's invite him to the table.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.87,0:11:07.26,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Bring him.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.30,0:11:09.73,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,That's a flute, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.84,0:11:10.56,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.90,0:11:12.06,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,I remember you!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:12.17,0:11:14.11,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,You are the genius boy\Nflute player David...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.17,0:11:16.17,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,who won the championship\Nat the last competition.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.28,0:11:19.58,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,If you know me, then please\Nreturn me to the surface!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.05,0:11:21.01,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Please!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.11,0:11:22.84,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,That's impossible.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.98,0:11:26.85,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,I want you to remain\Na hostage just in case.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.72,0:11:28.92,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,How come?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:30.66,0:11:32.22,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Didn't you find any clues?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.39,0:11:34.62,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Unfortunately, I still\Nhaven't found anything.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.80,0:11:37.85,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,As I feared.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:38.37,0:11:40.23,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Miss, please don't be disappointed.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.37,0:11:42.93,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sure there is\Nsome way to find him.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.07,0:11:45.77,Thought,,0000,0000,0000,,There was nothing at\Nthe bottom of the river.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.87,0:11:50.47,Thought,,0000,0000,0000,,There is only one person who could\Nconceive and carry out a ruse like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.62,0:12:02.61,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Here goes!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.36,0:12:05.19,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Holmes, be careful!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.33,0:12:06.29,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,I know.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.63,0:12:10.86,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, the tide is on the ebb.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.24,0:12:20.33,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,David!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.61,0:12:24.30,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey! Watch out!\NWhat are you?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.91,0:12:27.47,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Let me go!\NI saw David over there!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.61,0:12:28.84,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Miss, it's just your imagination.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:33.52,0:12:34.89,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,What was I doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:35.02,0:12:37.92,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, you gave me quite a scare.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.02,0:12:39.32,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm very sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.27,0:12:51.74,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Watson, let's check from\Nthe boat one more time!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.84,0:12:52.70,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.54,0:12:57.53,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Holmes, what's going on?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.26,0:13:16.79,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,I believe we've found the\Nmonster's hideout.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.00,0:13:17.93,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Take a look.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.10,0:13:19.19,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Let me see.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.43,0:13:22.87,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,That steel plate must be\Nthe entrance of the hideout.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.74,0:13:26.60,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,But it's under water.\NUnder steel plates as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.77,0:13:28.74,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,It won't be easy to open.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.51,0:13:32.81,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's get some help from\Ninspector Lestrade and the Navy.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.82,0:13:37.81,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,This is...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.45,0:13:39.55,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Here's the trick...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.55,0:13:42.18,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,the monster comes out, swallowing\Nthe cargo ship loaded with goods.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.29,0:13:43.19,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Surprised?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.29,0:13:44.45,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,This is an amazing machine.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.79,0:13:46.76,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,But I'm sure somebody\Nwill find this soon!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.93,0:13:47.92,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm afraid not.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.03,0:13:51.69,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Not only Inspector Lestrade,\Nbut the famous Detective Holmes...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.76,0:13:52.70,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,is having a hard time\Ninvestigating this case.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.70,0:13:53.53,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,He's already given up.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.73,0:13:54.89,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Mr. Holmes?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.34,0:13:57.93,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, not because Holmes didn't have\Nthe ability to figure this out...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.00,0:14:01.06,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,it's just that my genius brain is\Nsuperior, and has brought me victory.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.65,0:14:12.71,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Fortunately we found\Nan old scrap ship.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.39,0:14:15.62,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,We will decorate it and make it\Nlook like a new ship now.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.06,0:14:17.78,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you for your cooperation.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:17.89,0:14:19.72,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, let's move on quickly!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.86,0:14:22.52,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,But be careful with those goods!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.26,0:14:26.23,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Inspector, how long will it take?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.90,0:14:29.66,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I think they can finish loading\Nthe goods in about one hour.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.11,0:14:33.40,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Then, we have to hurry too.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:33.94,0:14:38.54,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, Holmes, are you sure we can beat\Nthe monster just by doing this?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.75,0:14:41.58,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Everything is perfect.\NPlease do just as we have planned.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.69,0:14:50.99,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,If the enemy made a\Nfortification under the river...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.22,0:14:54.63,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,they have to have\Na place to let in air.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.63,0:14:58.10,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,But, so far I can't find\Nthe spot anywhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.46,0:15:03.56,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,I might have overlooked it.\NMaybe we should go back again.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.58,0:15:10.84,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Mr. Holmes?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.91,0:15:11.97,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.25,0:15:13.37,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Holmes!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.98,0:15:18.61,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,I brought the longest\Nrope, just like you asked.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.72,0:15:19.62,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.69,0:15:21.71,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Did you find any clues?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.82,0:15:23.15,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,I already found one.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.52,0:15:26.08,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,There is no need for a\Nchimney in a warehouse.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.83,0:15:28.82,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you think you can\Ncatch anything today?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.00,0:15:31.40,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,So far, I've only seen a small barge.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.90,0:15:33.30,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,You don't have to rush.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.43,0:15:36.03,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sure a big target will appear soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.18,0:15:50.08,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Mary, I won't give up until the end.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.84,0:16:11.06,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Here you go.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.11,0:16:14.57,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,I can hear David playing the flute.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.28,0:16:20.27,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,David.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.71,0:16:23.58,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sure this must be connected\Nto the underwater fortification.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.42,0:16:29.72,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,It sounds very noisy.\NLet me stop his playing.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.82,0:16:30.72,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.36,0:16:35.92,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Beautiful music is great nutrition\Nfor the genius brain.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.06,0:16:37.55,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Make sure he keeps playing.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.70,0:16:40.46,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, but I have a bad feeling.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.07,0:16:46.37,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Mr. Holmes, be careful.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.47,0:16:47.50,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.81,0:16:49.27,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Can you tell Inspector Lestrade...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.34,0:16:51.40,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,to have the ship\Nleave in five minutes.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.64,0:16:52.94,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,All right, I will.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.49,0:17:04.18,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Now begins the extermination\Nof the monster...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.86,0:17:07.26,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,and we will rescue David.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.50,0:17:14.90,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Is anything wrong?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.23,0:17:16.39,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,The flute stopped.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.47,0:17:18.77,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,W... who are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.54,0:17:22.06,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm Holmes, I'm here to take you back.\NHere, come quickly.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.18,0:17:23.27,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.11,0:17:29.21,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Todd, can you go and tell him\Nto keep playing the flute?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.28,0:17:30.27,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.62,0:17:34.61,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,What's that noise?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:35.29,0:17:36.81,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,It sounds very suspicious.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.30,0:17:44.36,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Professor!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.36,0:17:45.06,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.06,0:17:46.77,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,I see a big ship coming close to us.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.77,0:17:47.36,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.27,0:17:54.47,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Lestrade!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.98,0:17:58.53,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,The Inspector is guarding it himself.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.68,0:18:00.98,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,That ship must be carrying\Nvery valuable goods.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.11,0:18:03.08,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,This is going to be a big catch.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.11,0:18:05.67,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Professor, what about his flute?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.89,0:18:06.94,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Fool!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.02,0:18:10.18,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,This is not a time to worry about it.\NHurry! Hurry up!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.26,0:18:11.38,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Go into the action right now!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.49,0:18:13.12,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Wait for me!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.02,0:18:38.81,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Great, reverse the engine.\NMove Point Two to the right.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.37,0:18:56.23,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,The distance to the\Ntarget is thirty meters.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.30,0:18:57.33,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Turn on the light.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.98,0:19:05.81,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Inspector, it's here!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.76,0:19:16.74,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Great!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.82,0:19:18.62,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, ignite the fuses!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.07,0:19:29.63,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Close the lid tightly.\NIf water gets in, we're finished.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:46.79,0:19:47.88,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Abandon ship!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.02,0:19:49.21,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Hurry!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.87,0:20:08.86,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,We did it! A great success!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.01,0:20:10.77,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,What are the goods this time?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.91,0:20:12.57,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,They had heavy security.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.68,0:20:14.58,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sure it will be gold bullion.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.71,0:20:15.98,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Gold bullion?!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.08,0:20:18.41,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,We can eat gourmet food again!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.67,0:20:42.73,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,We did it!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.51,0:20:49.41,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey Holmes, it's them again.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.52,0:20:50.35,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.42,0:20:55.48,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't let them go!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.13,0:21:06.60,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Moriarty! I will arrest you this time!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.23,0:21:09.76,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Curses!\NYou get more annoying every week!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.10,0:21:11.26,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Here we go!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.54,0:21:14.03,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Fools!\NWhy don't you come and catch us?!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.48,0:21:19.44,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.31,0:21:21.64,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Take that!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.75,0:21:30.35,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,That's as far as you go!\NEnjoy your rest!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.99,0:21:33.22,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey! Do a U turn! A U turn!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.57,0:21:49.47,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Go!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.08,0:21:53.20,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't let them go!\NGo! Move! Move!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.15,0:21:56.88,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Even through fire and water!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.12,0:22:07.75,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,I have a great respect for\NInspector Lestrade's fighting spirit.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.89,0:22:09.22,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, that's true.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.43,0:22:11.92,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,You won another victory\Nwith this case.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:12.03,0:22:12.73,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:17.80,0:22:21.20,Text,,0000,0000,0000,,Their love is the real victory.
